享年72岁。"},"hr":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21. ožujka 1697.–1769.","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720.–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769.","1720":"1720.","1797":"1797","November 1752":"studeni 1752.","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21. ožujka 1697.","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769.","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, Sjedinjene Države"},"cs":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21. března 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"listopad 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21. března 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pensylvánie, Spojené státy"},"da":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21. marts 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"november 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21. marts 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Skotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, Amerikas Forenede Stater"},"nl":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21 maart 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"november 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21 maart 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Schotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, Verenigde Staten van Amerika"},"en":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21 March 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"November 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21 March 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, United States","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cameron","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:","in the Highlands, it is usually a nickname from Gaelic <i>cam</i> ‘crooked, bent’ + <i>sròn</i> ‘nose’.","in the Lowlands it is also a habitational name from any of various places called Cameron, especially in Fife."],"variants":[{"name":"Camren","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Cameron  ."]},{"name":"Cambron","meanings":["Spanish (<b>Cambrón</b>): habitational name from any of several places in the provinces of Cáceres and Murcia called Cambrón.","Scottish: altered form of   Cameron  .","French: habitational name from any of the places in Somme and Aisne called Cambron. Alternatively, from a diminutive of <i>c(h)ambre</i> ‘room’ (see   Cambre  )."]},{"name":"Camron","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Cameron  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":5001005,"age":51,"year":"1749","julianDay":2359870,"description":"Historical Boundaries: 1749: York, Pennsylvania Colony, British Colonial America 1776: York, Pennsylvania, United States","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Cameron was born on 21 March 1697, in Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Dr. John Linn. She died in 1769, in York, Pennsylvania, United States, at the age of 72."},"et":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21. märts 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"november 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21. märts 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, Ameerika Ühendriigid"},"fi":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21. maaliskuuta 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"marraskuu 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21. maaliskuuta 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvania, Yhdysvallat"},"fr":{"21 March 1697–1769":"21 mars 1697–1769","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1720–1797":"1720–1797","1697–1769":"1697–1769","1720":"1720","1797":"1797","November 1752":"novembre 1752","1697":"1697","1752":"1752","21 March 1697":"21 mars 1697","1695":"1695","1749":"1749","1769":"1769","Augusta, Virginia, British Colonial America":"Augusta, Virginie, Amérique coloniale britannique","Comrie, Perthshire, Scotland":"Comrie, Perthshire, Écosse","York, Pennsylvania, United States":"York, Pennsylvanie, États-Unis","lifeSummary":"Margaret Cameron est née le 21 mars 1697, à Comrie, Perthshire, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Dr. John Linn. Elle est décédée en 1769, à York, Pennsylvanie, États-Unis, à l’âge 